Worker is a separate process to run the test cases.
Each worker runs single files at a time
1 worker = only 1 file runs at a time
2 workers - 2 files can run at the same time. This is called parallel at file level


Inside one file:

Test1
Test2
Test3

By default:
👉 They run one by one (NOT parallel).
-------------------------------------------------------


fullyParallel = true
This means:
👉 Tests inside the file can run together
-------------------------------------------------
workers = 2
fullyParallel = false    - This is recommended

File1 and File2 run together
👉 But inside each file → tests run one by one

✔ Safe
✔ Used in real projects

---------------------------------------------------
workers = 2
fullyParallel = true

👉 File1 + File2 run together
👉 AND tests inside also run together

⚡ Very fast
❌ Can cause issues (data clash, login conflicts)
---------------------------------------------

Final Understanding:

👉 workers = how many files run together
👉 fullyParallel = tests inside file run together or not

----------------------------------------------------------

“If fullyParallel is enabled, tests inside a file run simultaneously,
which can cause issues like shared session conflicts. So in real projects, 
we keep fullyParallel false and rely on multiple workers for safe parallel execution.”